<b>Hyperspace</b> is an instant-on <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../194/22194.xml">
operating system</link> that is being developed by <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../470/3031470.xml">
Phoenix Technologies</link></company>
.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> <p>

The operating system will be <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../934/18934934.xml">
read-only memory</link> based and as such may only apply to <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../945/19945.xml">
motherboards</link> which have this operating system embedded.</p>
<p>

It will allow users to use a web browser, word processor, and many other applications while you wait for the operating system to boot. It can also be used to avoid the security problems associated with using the <link>
 Windows</link> operating system, or for troubleshooting.</p>

